{"commentv2": 1, "number": 6, "id": 88539, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "18361", "body": "The infernals have been nerfed a LOT, and no longer can 2-shot cloth wearers. In addition, the channeler's spells have longer cast times and can be interrupted more easily. Overall, a pretty big nerf to this encounter", "date": "2007-05-23T14:25:05-05:00", "rating": 22, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Also, the Channeler's health has been reduced by 1/3. making the encounter much more manageable.", "creationdate": "2007-06-07T19:04:37-05:00", "id": 300677, "rating": 0, "commentid": 88539, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "54241", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "There seems to be some issue with Hunters clicking Manticron Cubes whilst Auto-shot is active, two of our hunters have had issues with the auto-shot somehow triggering the cube as soon as they get in range of it, or interrupting the cube-channelling once they've clicked it - can anyone verify if this is a known issue, please?", "creationdate": "2007-07-31T03:40:31-05:00", "id": 12478, "rating": 16, "commentid": 88539, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Juyo", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I can confirm this issue.  I was in Magtheridon and while I was still in range with Authoshot still on, it cancelled my clicking and wiped the raid.  Hunters just need to make sure that they take off Autoshot before clicking or they will cancell the casting to attack.  It did NOT however give me the debuff when I cancelled the casting for some odd reason.", "creationdate": "2008-06-18T21:59:48-05:00", "id": 36744, "rating": 3, "commentid": 88539, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "39249", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Well now as a hunter myself, at lvl 90 it doesn't matter if you even see a cube. each time I do the raid solo I distroy him way before anything happens.", "creationdate": "2012-12-27T15:03:59-06:00", "id": 616356, "rating": -1, "commentid": 88539, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "RiftWalker", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 7, "id": 135394, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "jcj64200031", "body": "Anyone know how long you have to get out of a cave-in?", "date": "2007-08-10T11:37:29-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 8, "id": 151604, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "17130", "body": "When we started Magtheridon, we found it helpful to have the RL assign icons to the guys who had to click the next queue. I'd make two macros that auto-assigned icons to predetermined players, it would look something like this:\r\n\r\n[quote]Macro 1:\r\n/script SetRaidTarget(\"target A\",index)\r\n/script SetRaidTarget(\"target B\",index)\r\n/script SetRaidTarget(\"target C\",index)\r\n/script SetRaidTarget(\"target D\",index)\r\n/script SetRaidTarget(\"target E\",index)[/quote]\r\n\r\nI'd replace Target A-E with player names in my raid, Index would be a number from 1-8:\r\n\r\n[quote]0 = no icon \r\n1 = Yellow 4-point Star \r\n2 = Orange Circle \r\n3 = Purple Diamond \r\n4 = Green Triangle \r\n5 = White Crescent Moon \r\n6 = Blue Square \r\n7 = Red \"X\" Cross \r\n8 = White Skull[/quote]\r\n\r\nI'd have two version of this macro, with the same icons but different guys (obviously). The icons would correspond to the icons we assigned the channelers standing by the cube before we start the fight.\r\n\r\nThat way a Cube would \"become\" the star-cube, x-cube, etc., and we would have an easier time communicating.\r\n\r\nWhenever a cube had been clicked, I'd activate the other macro and raid icons would move from the first group, to the second group of clickers. No one would ever mess up in whether it was their turn or not in this way, and as RL I could easily survey whether all 5 guys were up by looking for the icons.\r\n\r\n/Mythicow, Esoteric Foundation, Defias Brotherhood", "date": "2007-09-11T09:39:26-05:00", "rating": 41, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Fantastic idea.", "creationdate": "2007-09-21T01:52:29-05:00", "id": 311707, "rating": 1, "commentid": 151604, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "58622", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 9, "id": 159432, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "samarium", "body": "Specific to Hunters:\r\n\r\nBe sure to disable Auto-Shot when it comes time for you to click your cube.  I accidentally left it on and lag caused my next shot to break my channeling, Exhausting my Mind and wiping my raid.\r\n\r\nEmbarrassing.", "date": "2007-09-27T13:55:03-05:00", "rating": 36, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 10, "id": 169838, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Snazzy", "body": "To people who's about to try this guy:\r\n\r\nMy raid usually used a warrior to tank this guy - our warrior had 3/5 t4, and 1/5 t5, etc etc. \r\n\r\nHe was hitting the warrior for 7k dmg max, while when I tried to tank him (4/5), (I'm a feral druid by the way) hitted me for 5k max, this is really something you should take into consideration, we found it way easier to let druids tank him.", "date": "2007-10-16T14:22:05-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 11, "id": 181117, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "jcj64200031", "body": "new in patch 2.3:\r\n\r\n[quote]Hellfire Citadel: Magtheridon's Lair \r\nMind Exhaustion is not applied until Magtheridon is successfully banished.[/quote]\r\n\r\nso while you'll still need a main clicker, a 2nd clicker, and a backup clicker (for if someone dies) you no longer have to worry about clicking twice or moving accidentaly after you click.", "date": "2007-11-08T17:17:49-06:00", "rating": 10, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 12, "id": 197187, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "103365", "body": "The 2.3 change to the Mind Exhaustion debuff makes this fight considerably less sensitive to wipes caused by things like latency, delayed loading of the channeling graphic, or simple accidental misclicks. However, this remains the most challenging T4 encounter to organize and plan. Assignment macros and an addon like Orion Magtheridon Assist can greatly simplify the preparation involved in staging an attempt.\r\n\r\nA complete guide to killing Magtheridon, including assignment macros and a link to the OMA addon, can be found at http://www.worldofstrats.com/Magtheridon/tabid/60/Default.aspx", "date": "2007-12-07T00:20:11-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 13, "id": 198994, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Mister6002", "body": "Since patch 2.3, u now get the 'Champion of the Naaru' q when u did / do the attunement quest for The Eye.", "date": "2007-12-10T09:57:53-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "You also have to complete \"The Cudgel of Kardesh\" - the SSC attunement quest that is not required for attunement anymore, but is still in the game.  A couple of people in my guild who were all psyched to get the title after killing Magtheridon, but who had skipped that quest.  Oops - back to Nightbane & Gruul & heroic Slave Pens.", "creationdate": "2008-01-15T08:38:29-06:00", "id": 23225, "rating": 7, "commentid": 198994, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "43740", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 14, "id": 203720, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Kaitain", "body": "Contrary to a lot of other bosses in TBC and contrary to what a lot of guilds think, this fight is not a DPS race at all, you simply need control. Once you learn to control the Infernals in phase 1 and interupt all the casting from the channelers, you should arrive at phase 2 healthy and ready to DPS Mag. From there the raid takes almost no damage and you will probably have an excess of healing to keep the MT topped at all times. Just go nice and steady and keep on top of the clicking.", "date": "2007-12-19T03:25:55-06:00", "rating": 14, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2007-12-19T03:26:32-06:00", 1, "Kaitain"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 15, "id": 232688, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "122037", "body": "whos harder gruul, or mag? and can a guild in kara epics with mismatter glad do mag?", "date": "2008-02-10T10:29:15-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I'd say you can, but it's gonna be tough on your MT and his healers. Maggy is definitely tougher than Gruul, but luckily a tad less dependant on sheer luck.", "creationdate": "2008-02-14T02:53:58-06:00", "id": 25714, "rating": 5, "commentid": 232688, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Carighan", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 16, "id": 237624, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "16109", "body": "Changed on 2.4 PTR -- no infernals and 30 sec mind exhaustion instead of 85, so you need only 5 clickers for the whole fight.", "date": "2008-02-16T18:50:54-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Yet still safe to assign a few backup people in case the freak accidental death happens, somehow.  Unfortunately they've really nerfed the encounter. It wasn't that difficult pre-2.3, either.", "creationdate": "2008-02-16T21:05:55-06:00", "id": 25967, "rating": 6, "commentid": 237624, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Kaneiac", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 17, "id": 237792, "nreplies": 7, "sticky": 0, "user": "vaeal", "body": "The following are rumored (unconfirmed) nerfs that the Magtheridon encounter will recieve in 2.4\r\n\r\nhttp://boards.worldofraids.com/topic-11013-1.html\r\nthere are 3 channelers instead of 5\r\nthere are 3 cubes instead of 5\r\nthere is only 1 infernal per channeler\r\nthe boss doesn't have a cleave attack anymore\r\nthe ceiling damage has be reduced roughly by half\r\nthe cube debuff decreased from 75 seconds duration to 30seconds", "date": "2008-02-17T03:00:30-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Killed on the test realm for 2.4  - Infernals reduced to one per channeler (used to be two) - Mind Exhausion reduced to 30s - Yes he does still cleave - There are still 5 channelers - Unsure on the ceiling damage  Also his loot is substantially buffed: - A non-unique 20 slot bag - a bag of epic gems - ~500g - 3x Badge of Justice - 3x T4 tokens - Usual random epics - Head", "creationdate": "2008-02-17T22:58:37-06:00", "id": 26061, "rating": 30, "commentid": 237792, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "110634", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Have screenshots for proof? If so, I'm glad. Maybe it will make people more encouraged to kill Magtheridon now instead of skipping him. :)", "creationdate": "2008-02-18T22:53:32-06:00", "id": 326096, "rating": 0, "commentid": 237792, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Kaneiac", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "20g for something that takes longer than two dailies? It certainly enough, but definitely not too much.  EDIT: How many epic gems in the bag?", "creationdate": "2008-02-20T15:28:53-06:00", "id": 326342, "rating": 1, "commentid": 237792, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Benegesserit", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Magtheridon is very easy kill in 2.4 - you only need one set of \"cube-clickers\". There are rumors, thou... In 2.5 Magtheridon will have to click cubes on his own, and if not, the raid goes enrage and wipes him in no time.", "creationdate": "2008-04-04T09:30:13-05:00", "id": 30118, "rating": 56, "commentid": 237792, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Kwinto", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "The bag he drops is now unique: http://www.wowhead.com/?item=34845", "creationdate": "2008-04-24T19:24:26-05:00", "id": 31885, "rating": 8, "commentid": 237792, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "47151", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 18, "id": 241678, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "7784", "body": "http://www.wowhead.com/?item=34846\n\nThis seems to be the bag that Magtheridon drops in 2.4.  No idea on it's contents.", "date": "2008-02-22T22:49:39-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Also, there's been confirmation on the 20 slot bag.  http://www.worldofraids.com/2008/ptr/24/mag-bag.jpg  Plus the wowhead page on it.", "creationdate": "2008-02-25T17:31:17-06:00", "id": 326926, "rating": 0, "commentid": 241678, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Kaneiac", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Black Sack of Gems contained 3 epic quality and some blue quality gems for us.", "creationdate": "2008-02-27T02:01:16-06:00", "id": 327096, "rating": 2, "commentid": 241678, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Vesper", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-03-04T15:22:24-06:00", 1, "7784"]}
