{"commentv2": 1, "number": 24, "id": 295159, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "153794", "body": "Magtheridon, the former Lord of Outland, is a Pit Lord who conquered the ruins of the orcish homeworld following its destruction. His reign was ended by the arrival of Illidan Stormrage, who took Magtheridon's throne at The Black Temple for himself. Deciding that Magtheridon would have a further part to play, Illidan had Magtheridon's body dragged to the Hellfire Citadel where he imprisoned the Pit Lord, leaving him at the mercy of the fel orcs. His rumbling cries are heard throughout the Hellfire Citadel. It is interesting to note that his wardens are not fel orcs, but normal green-skinned orcs. It seems that Illidan is keeping Magtheridon alive for the sole reason to create more fel orcs under his rule.", "date": "2008-05-26T18:37:33-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 25, "id": 304345, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "bkevol", "body": "i discovered that at 30% when he caves in the roof on every1. if i moved around i took triple the damage but if i just stood still i only took the 5k or whatever it is. dont move.. my raid did unfortunately get Quake on most of the dps/healers/ clickers during that cave in once. and wiped us because we were moving.  Is there a timer on quake or is it just random. starting 40secs after he activates?", "date": "2008-06-13T12:05:18-05:00", "rating": 24, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Just before 30%, remember that mages can iceblock and paladins can bubble and bop a companion to avoid taking the 6k physical damage to the face. I guess it was pretty obvious that that would be a smart thing to do, but I didn't think of it until I got it shouted at me on TS. I hope that helps someone.", "creationdate": "2008-06-16T19:35:58-05:00", "id": 36538, "rating": 19, "commentid": 304345, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "118228", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "anyone who moves will take double damage while its caving in and i guess people would rather give me a \"minus\" rating for asking a question instead of answering it above", "creationdate": "2008-06-26T12:55:16-05:00", "id": 37627, "rating": 14, "commentid": 304345, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "bkevol", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
