{"commentv2": 1, "number": 40, "id": 832703, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Carusun", "body": "So, my gf and I are going through some of the old world end game dungeons, and after our success with Onyxia, she was wondering if we would have a chance with some of the BC endgame stuff as well...\r\n\r\nWould we stand any chance at downing Maggy whatsoever? \r\n\r\nOur chars can be found [url=http://eu.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=The+Venture+Co&n=Atriusun]here[/url] and [url=http://eu.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=The+Venture+Co&n=Saishoku]here[/url]\r\n\r\nI'll probably be using my Demo spec.\r\n\r\nAny advice and/or warnings would be great, I know our gear isn't too good, but we are too scared of human contact to do heroics/raiding :P", "date": "2009-09-05T14:50:09-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 41, "id": 908271, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "235651", "body": "2 manned me and healer. to 20% twice(took toong to keep trying)\r\n\r\nProblem: at 30% he changes, and once at 20% we both died instanly, 2nd time 1 died he want near me. Ceiling callapse yea...but how to avoid? whats the best strategy>?\r\n\r\nSide Problem(doesnt matter): all adds dont die, tanked them and boss but with no problem.... so not a problem actualy lol", "date": "2009-12-07T05:35:52-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 42, "id": 956849, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "197116", "body": "Solo'd this bad boy today. Blood DK tank, about 43k HP, just tanked all 5 channelers and infernals from pull through to mag's death. Not sure how close to enrage it was, but all 500ish gold straight into my pocket. Will be fun doing this weekly for cash =D", "date": "2010-01-25T23:59:14-06:00", "rating": 9, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Solo'd as well, if you're a blood DK rocking decent tank gear, do this weekly for a nice gold boost.  I used [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?talent#jcEGqc0IcfRbosxhxZ0g:GdimV0]this[/url] spec.  Though it would of been far better to replace Death Strike with Pestilence glyph; the DPS loss from DS would be made up by the extra heart strike every 20 seconds.  Tank them (adds + mag) in one of the corners - I used the northwest - and burn Mag once he's free.  Use raise ghoul after he finishes casting blast wave and don't be afraid to use cooldowns every time they come up.  Just remember to save AMS fo", "creationdate": "2010-01-25T23:59:15-06:00", "id": 446558, "rating": 1, "commentid": 956849, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Lolquile", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 43, "id": 975008, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Nzall", "body": "it might be possible for a protection paladin to solo this.\n\nblast wave has a 60 seconds CD. this means that if you have 2 2 minute CD defensive cooldowns (divine protection and divine guardian-buffed divine sacrifice), you could chain CD's for this.\n\nnormally, blast wave does 12.5K damage. divine protection makes 6.25K from that. divine sacrifice changes 12.5K to 10,250 damage. the 60 seconds between blast waves could mean you could heal that back up in between with SoL and JoL.\n\nedit: i have been thinking about combining sacrifice and hand of salvation glyphed for the second CD. this would mean a DR of 44%, or about 7K damage taken. also, we have about 21% damage reduction on magical damage from talents and buffs. this means blast wave deals 9,875 damage over those 10 seconds. this means bubblewall reduces that to 4,937.5, and the other CD reduces it to 5,530 damage.\n\nthe other big chasm is the enrage timer of 20 minutes. this means i need to do 2,810 DPS to get it. however, if i need to keep my HP up, i will need to have some HP boosts up.", "date": "2010-02-13T09:55:16-06:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Just wanted to add that the Blast Wave is probably your least concern in this fight as a Protection Paladin. His melee and Cleave hit much harder, so the time it takes him to cast a Blast Wave is actually god-send.  I tried a few different approaches of this fight;  First going in normally with a slightly tweaked spec, though mainly based on survivability. This led to a wipe due to Enrage at 19%, but no problem with surviving at any time.  Going in with a more dps-focused spec and lots of dps consumables, I eventually got killed by the high damage while still struggling to stay ahead of the en", "creationdate": "2010-02-13T09:55:17-06:00", "id": 449771, "rating": 1, "commentid": 975008, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "336631", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-02-25T14:03:45-06:00", 1, "Nzall"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 44, "id": 975187, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "24258", "body": "I soloed him too today as a blood DK w/ pestilence, took me 4 tries to get it, but it was worth it in the end.\r\n\r\nIt took me 21 minutes and 58 seconds on the kill though, and that was with using army/ghoul and Hysteria every cooldown. Also pretty much needed all my other abilities to stay alive, but it was enough in the end. And so worth it.", "date": "2010-02-13T13:46:22-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
