{"commentv2": 1, "number": 47, "id": 1015941, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "483682", "body": "Took me a while to notice, but you can see him under the floor in Keli'Dan the Breaker's room. (Blood Furnace)", "date": "2010-04-09T11:22:00-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 48, "id": 1039870, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "sorsa", "body": "Z\u00f3dd - Hellscream ~5.05k GS DK with 41k UB health, managed to get him down on the 3rd try with heavy struggle and careful rationing of CDs. Used a customized version of Blood/Unholy-38/33 (inspired by Raegwyn's Blood-Unholy solo build), which you can check out in my armory profile:\r\n\r\nhttp://eu.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=Hellscream&cn=Z%C3%B3dd\r\n\r\nBy constantly spamming Rune Strike and keeping ghoul frenzied I managed to average out at a round 3015 single target dps on Mag (without disease aoe), ending the fight about 19mins after the pull. 5k GS seems to be scratching at border of the doable though.. the first 2 tries there were moments where even chaining all my available CDs couldn't keep me up during damage spikes, and on the kill I had to utilise Dark Pact 3 times to stay alive.\r\n\r\nIn order to beat the enrage timer I uses Citadel Enforcer's claymore with Fallen Crusader, and swapped in a few pieces of hit to reach 8% meele hit cap and 23 expertice. One observation during these fights was that the 3% self heal from Fallen Crusader procs is an immense help to survivability, as it chain procs constantly.\r\n\r\nAn extremely thrilling fight, good luck to all you Mag hunters out there!", "date": "2010-05-16T11:01:05-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 49, "id": 1066033, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Alspaladin", "body": "done it with 3 ppl\r\nholy pala - me\r\nferal dru - dps\r\nprot warr - tank\r\n\r\ntank grabs all mobs and moves them to the wall, dps takes one caster at a time, moves him to the opposite side of the room and kills him there\r\none by one, do not worry about time, try to do as much interrupts as possible when mobs try to heal\r\n\r\nwhen phase2 starts, nothing changes except some benign quakes and boss hitting tank for a little.\r\ncontinue doing as before until all of the summoners are down\r\nthen just dps boss, do not worry about cubes, damage from boss is easy healable, just zerg him and get your free gold xD\r\n\r\nNOTE: warr tank makes fight very easy because he can:\r\n1) interrupt by himself\r\n2) cast vigilance on healer thus rapidly take infernals from healer", "date": "2010-06-25T15:35:55-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 50, "id": 1091867, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "MasakiKudo", "body": "We just 2 manned him, prot pally/ret pally.\r\n\r\nAs prot (me) I used seal of light, and any self heals I could as well as any migation (corroded skele key/sacred shield) and hold aggro on everything. \r\n\r\nWe found out that the channelers just kept on healing themselves and eachother so we didnt have the dps power to get them down quick enough with 1 dps pally and a prot pally so we just waited out the first phase, they didnt hit for very hard. Second phase came along, I picked up boss and had the ret pally heal through the blast novas, since all he had to do was holy light himself and me if he needed to and get mana back with seal of wisdom. About down to 1M HP he went into phase 3, collapsed the walls and stuff. Blah blah blah, same old thing, and we downed him. \r\n\r\nHe dropped a couple pieces, handguards, his head, tier pieces, and we got about 238g each, so all in all it was a good run. The trash I had solo'd before the boss, it was a pain the ass -_-", "date": "2010-07-29T20:03:56-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 51, "id": 1102799, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "EmbrceYrInnrGeek", "body": "Two manned this guy yesterday using a shadow priest + Prot pally who's keeping an extra eye on the infernal spawns to avoid unecessary damage on the priest. \r\nThe vampire embrace spell almost healed the damage of the Blast Nova between the gaps of his casts and the paladin had no problem keeping himself alive with no heals from me using SoL, JoL & Sacred Shield.\r\n\r\nGot him down in about 7 Minutes with an approxiate single target DPS of:\r\n\r\nPaladin: 900\r\nPriest: 5900\r\n\r\nTotal: 6800\r\n\r\n[b]He still drops 500 gold pieces split![/b] So its DEFINATELY worth going here with a great 2 man setup to harvest the 250g for maximum 15 minutes of effort.\r\n\r\n[b][u]JUST DONT TANK MAGTHERIDON AND HIS ADDS CLOSE THE ENTERING GATE. HIS PUSHBACK WILL MOST LIKELY PUSH YOU TOWARDS IT AND RESET THE WHOLE ENCOUNTER =)[/u][/b]", "date": "2010-08-18T02:19:15-05:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Comfortably soloable as a Blood Death Knight without any raiding gear (I was at iLevel 346 when I first did it). I have one crafted epic (belt) and the rep epics from Ramkahen and Guardians of Hyjal.  Strategy is very simple, pull the Channellers and just tank them for the entire fight. Your Death Strike should be healing you more than enough to tank them indefinitely, even with all 5 Infernals and Magtheridon smacking you as well. Takes roughly 10-12 minutes to solo. Just make sure to keep refreshing your diseases on Magtheridon and spreading them over the adds with Pestilence.  You can use A", "creationdate": "2010-08-18T02:19:16-05:00", "id": 479022, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1102799, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Anarial", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "can't emphisise the last bit enough: [u][b]JUST DONT TANK MAGTHERIDON AND HIS ADDS CLOSE THE ENTERING GATE. HIS PUSHBACK WILL MOST LIKELY PUSH YOU TOWARDS IT AND RESET THE WHOLE ENCOUNTER =)[/b][/u] having him reset at 10% just isn't funny : /", "creationdate": "2010-08-25T19:14:39-05:00", "id": 179171, "rating": 3, "commentid": 1102799, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "halgarth", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Ive been doing Mag's every week for a while now, but the random resets are starting to get REALLY annoying... like tonight I had 1 sub 900k and 2 sub 500k resets... not fun.  Anyone know why this happens? I've been tanking him in the back of the room, furthest away from the gate, and he still resets, always during or right after a Quake.", "creationdate": "2010-10-06T00:20:56-05:00", "id": 185233, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1102799, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "285085", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 52, "id": 1105562, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "543999", "body": "Ok, Blizzard was REALLY lazy with the Pit Lords in WOW, Magtheridon was purple in Warcraft 3 and Mannoroth was greyish green and had black armor, but they all looks the same green with red armor in WOW, the only pit lord that got a special skin was Brutallus, and he didn't even have a backstory!", "date": "2010-08-22T07:31:35-05:00", "rating": 13, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 53, "id": 1125138, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "622529", "body": "Think he can be soloed as a prot paladin?", "date": "2010-09-21T19:08:10-05:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "my paly  :P   http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UlvzJuCjJV4", "creationdate": "2010-10-26T16:44:38-05:00", "id": 188851, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1125138, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "lylyt", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 54, "id": 1168970, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "618266", "body": "Attempted to solo Magtheridon on my warrior last night. It didn't end well. Trash was easy enough, but the adds on the Mag fight just put out too much (magic) damage for Blood Craze and Bloodthirst to heal through. I barely survived the opening phase and bit it right after Mag activated.\r\n\r\nFor reference, I was wearing Protection gear (including 4pt10) with an average item level of 260. I was using a slightly modified Fury spec designed for soloing.\r\n\r\nI'm sure I could easily two-man this with an occasional heal. I imagine this will be soloable for a warrior at level 85 without much trouble.", "date": "2010-11-12T11:41:09-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 55, "id": 1174721, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "697693", "body": "Duo-ed with prot warrior and resto shaman.  Pretty easy.  We tried once with me as fury and it didn't work since you can't out damage the adds and need to leave them up.  Once I switched to prot it wasn't a problem.  It's okay to leave an infernal here or there on the shaman for water shield!\r\n\r\nSmooth sailing though and only took about 18 minutes!", "date": "2010-11-18T20:27:12-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 56, "id": 1245785, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "PilsnerDk", "body": "Solo'd as a lvl 85 protection paladin in blues, I estimate my average ilvl to be around 320. Complete piece of cake, took 16 minutes.", "date": "2010-12-19T14:18:31-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 57, "id": 1246800, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "389201", "body": "I attempted soloing this as a survival hunter with a bear, mostly 85 questing blues with a few greens. I tried to deal with the constant heals the adds gave each other until I gave up and let the encounter reset. \r\n\r\nkeeping my pet alive was barely an issue, and the shadow volleys barely left a dent, but the sheer amount of stalling was getting tedious. was kind of like fighting a training dummy with a retribution aura.\r\n\r\nI'll come back sometime with heroic gear and give it another go.", "date": "2010-12-19T23:51:15-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 58, "id": 1250460, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "andrewtabs", "body": "Soloed as an Unholy DK with an avg ilvl of 348. Took 6 minutes and 1 second. Hardest part was burning the first add or two before the healing got to be too overwhelming. Magtheridon himself was cake.", "date": "2010-12-21T13:40:32-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 59, "id": 1251441, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "237145", "body": "Just soloed by a 85 demonology warlock in blues / heroic gear.\r\n\r\nTook 2 attempts to get him down, first phase is easily the hardest.\r\nSince there are 5 channelers and they all heal, its very difficult to get passed.\r\nwhat i done was put my felguard on the first channeler and put my dots on him.\r\nBy the time all the other channelers reach the channeler you have dotted he should be around 80% \r\n\r\nWhen they are all grouped up, pop all cd's! metamorphosis > demon soul > summon infernal > immo aura > demonic leap > hellfire, and lasty pop your felguards felstorm\r\n\r\nat around 40% all the channelers will target the first channeler you dotted and cast dark mending on the one mob, by then all the channelers would have died exept for one (the one that got healed).\r\n\r\nDown the last channeler as usual and you should have alittle time to spare to heal before magtheridon is up.\r\n\r\nWhen he is up, the rest is easy! let your felguard get some agro and tank n spank! keep dots up and pop meta / cd's when they are up to down him quicker. If you get agro all you need to do is soulshatter!\r\nSo thats about it! enjoy your easy 500g / loot. :)", "date": "2010-12-22T01:03:46-06:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "soloed as lvl 85 DK - didnt feel like it fixing my spec or respecing, weak blood spec with just 1 point in improved blood tap and no bladed armor, average ilvl was 330,116 k hp... bla bla 1st tried to nuke adds but saw i cant do it, 2 despawns of maggy fallowed that, ended up with static tankig spot, healing throught all the adds and infernals stacking up scarlet fever and spamming heal cds = win", "creationdate": "2010-12-28T10:24:59-06:00", "id": 209089, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1251441, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "168133", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Tried to solo magtheridon as a 85 feral (hybrid spec) druid with ~333 average item level. I couldn't burst down the first set of five adds fast enough, even with berserk and 20k+ mangles being thrown on three targets at the same time.  Managed to get Magtheridon to 91% before I died.  I'm sure ferals would be able to solo it with higher level/tier gear.", "creationdate": "2010-12-31T11:11:45-06:00", "id": 210280, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1251441, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Etamalgren", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 60, "id": 1268703, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Herecius", "body": "Astoundingly simple to solo as a Beast Mastery Hunter. Don't even bother killing the adds, glyph mend pet, and constantly misdirect infernals to your pet. Fight takes a while, but you should never be in any danger. Simply stay at max range to keep from being shadowbolted by the channelers.", "date": "2010-12-30T21:36:03-06:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Might note that spirit bond is almost mandatory for this fight due to the blasts (unless you want to waste bandages, which are unreliable due to infernals and quakes), but then again, if you're bothering to solo old content you probably already have the talent.", "creationdate": "2011-01-06T12:07:51-06:00", "id": 212405, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1268703, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Alteir", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-12-31T17:01:50-06:00", 1, "Herecius"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 61, "id": 1274575, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "186899", "body": "Tried to solo this as a Blood DK, had no troubles staying alive, but I couldn't fight Mag for more than 2 minutes before he would despawn, every time.\r\nI suspect it might have something to do with my Bloodworms despawning/dying, because i've never had this problem before when duoing.\r\n\r\nJust a thought, in case anyone else comes here tryin to find an answer.", "date": "2011-01-03T05:35:43-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I'm having the exact same issue as a prot pally. He and all the others (channelers + infernals) despawn after what looks like the start of his second blast nova.  I don't know what it is, I've restarted the fight 3 times and he keeps de-spawning.  EDIT: Looks like the fourth time was a charm. I think what was happening is I was being knocked back into some small areas in the chamber that Mag cannot go into. (Perhaps clipping issue). I think since he would be unable to attack me it caused him to de-spawn. What I did this time was make sure I fought him in the center of the chamber. The other ti", "creationdate": "2011-01-03T05:35:44-06:00", "id": 474465, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1274575, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "46440", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 62, "id": 1274829, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "KryptoFreak", "body": "Soloed as enh shammy with full hc gear+some epics from rep reward and engineering.(also 2 epic pvp weapons)\r\n\r\nmy trick was to make my spirit wolves aggro the adds in the beginning furthers away, during the time I nuked the first one, then I did my best to  aoe them to like 50%, then I tried to interupt as many heals as possible, I managed to kill one add after another.\r\nMaggy aggroed me when the last add almost was dead, but luckily I had spirit wolves again to aggro him and save me from death.\r\n\r\nWhen adds were gone(including infernals) the rest was very easy,", "date": "2011-01-03T09:27:21-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 63, "id": 1279287, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "artyfarty", "body": "Was very bored and killed him in demo lock (me) and prot warrior 85's team.\r\n\r\nThe incoming damage was a joke, so i think it will be possible to solo it too.\r\n\r\nThe adds... I just AOEd them down all at once, thanks to demo's insane AOE damage.", "date": "2011-01-05T19:57:56-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 64, "id": 1282744, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Faradize", "body": "at lvl 85 as an enhancement shaman i was able to nuke the adds down very fast, interrupting the heals. the boss was 3 min.\r\nfast and good gold.", "date": "2011-01-07T17:15:49-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 65, "id": 1282883, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Hearthfiend", "body": "Can be soloed as an 85 protection paladin in mostly heroic blues.\r\n\r\nPull the trash in single groups, because their fear is nasty. \r\n\r\nDon't even try to kill the Channelers, they will heal too easily. Instead focus on Mag and use your cooldowns and word of glory often.", "date": "2011-01-07T19:19:29-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 66, "id": 1289852, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "spoonman184", "body": "Were the Channelers buffed to heal all of them? I couldn't AOE them down fast enough. Every time I tabbed over after seeing ONE of them heal, they were all bare minimum 90% hp.\n\n\nNevermind, need to Focus ONE of them down first so they ALL heal the same one.", "date": "2011-01-11T23:29:51-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-01-11T23:36:01-06:00", 1, "spoonman184"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 67, "id": 1290450, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "purpldrilmonkey", "body": "Solo'd last night as Demo Warlock. This might have actually been easier at lvl 80 in Wrath epics due to higer haste %\r\n\r\nMag is absolute cake, but getting the casters down is frustrating. I tried for about an hour to figure out a repeatable strat to get them down, and I finally came across one. Pure aoe didn''t work for me, and single target and tabbing didnt work - they all just healed through it\r\n\r\nProTip: summon your demonic circle outside the arena door and if you can't get the casters down, teleport out to reset.\r\n\r\nThe strat that worked for me:\r\n\r\nThe real trick I found is first to show thieir health bars with 'V'. Rather than tabbing through the mobs and hoping for low health, this lets you see who needs a nuke and who doesn't.\r\n\r\nSo,\r\n\r\nPull the first mob, dot him up and put your felguard on him. As the others run in, dot them up with at least corruption and I recommend immo for the MC procs. Now Felstorm, pop Meta, drop an infernal on them, and hit immo aura. The trick is to look for the lowest health bar after they heal someone. They shouldn't all heal themselves because the first mob you were hitting will ultimately need their heals. For me, at least one mob was below half health or lower. Click on their health bar and nuke that mob dead. Keep repeating this and hopefully you can kill 2 or 3 while the mass aoe is still ticking. I suggest popping felstorm a second time when you spot a mob with low health and it's ready again. Essentially, you want to keep all of their health ticking down but all at different levels so they can't properly distribute their heals. By showing their health bars, you can see when they make a mistake and leave one mob low on health.  All the other strats i tried failed for me, and the first time i showed their health bars and did this, it worked. Once three of them were down, I didn't even have to try the others dropped like flys.\r\n\r\nIf I recall, by stats are something like gear level 339, ~9% haste ~15% crit ~14% hit\r\nMore haste would help nuke, but you need hit since everything is lvl ?. If you miss any nukes tryinig to burn them you're screwed.\r\n\r\nOnce you engage Mag, its just a long Felguard tank and DoT kill. Nothing he does is big damage at all.", "date": "2011-01-12T09:51:31-06:00", "rating": 11, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 68, "id": 1296608, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "726951", "body": "I just managed to solo him as an 85 Death Knight, in tank spec but DPS gear, average of ilevel 342, having never done him in a group before.\r\n\r\nA couple of times I managed to make the mistake of not killing all the trash, so they ran in when I started on the channellers. Once they were all dead I managed to get him on the next attempt (somehow 6 extra mobs hitting and chain-fearing you makes the encounter harder). I also got one channeller down using Army of the Dead and one interrupt.\r\n\r\nI fought Magtheridon with my back against a wall to avoid despawning (had no problems at any time), I used my cooldowns when they were available, I kept Scarlet Fever and diseases up on all the enemies and basically just used heart strike and rune strike, with death strike every time it was available. I didn't go below 50% throughout the fight. I wouldn't call it easy, but then again I'm not incredibly geared and I probably made some mistakes.", "date": "2011-01-16T16:06:26-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 69, "id": 1300624, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Ademaren", "body": "Soloed as a Druid, Ademaren - EU Dun Modr, 30 minutes ago aprox.\r\n\r\nhttp://img138.imageshack.us/img138/6021/wowscrnshot011911210843.jpg\r\n\r\nBerserk + mangle to kill first adds, skull bash to cut heals, and a lot of patience. (22 minutes to me xD)", "date": "2011-01-19T14:41:49-06:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 70, "id": 1305251, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "127503", "body": "Just soloed this on my hunter. I couldn't kill the chanellers because of their heals, so I let my turtle tank them all. The infernals will continue to despawn and get resummoned, so keeping pet aggro on them is a pain. In the end I just kited them around Magtheridon while I killed him. I was Marksman for the heal from Chimaera shot, and I used the two-piece T5 bonus, although it wasn't really necessary.\r\n\r\nTrainwrecked.", "date": "2011-01-23T02:50:54-06:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 71, "id": 1310326, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "gugo0007", "body": "I soloes this on my balance druid last week its worth 500gold + loot", "date": "2011-01-26T06:38:31-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 72, "id": 1310807, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Saeed", "body": "As of 4.0.3, Magtheridon keeps on despawning at different stages of the fight for me. Sometimes at 2%, sometimes at 90%. Happened for me 4 times in a row, then finally could kill him again. Very annoying.\r\n\r\nAnyone else experencing the same thing?", "date": "2011-01-26T14:23:45-06:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Yes mate i got the same problem and i dont know how to fix it.  So instead of going there kill him in 10 min you have to waste 30-50min  to get your 500g becouse of this bug.", "creationdate": "2011-01-27T12:19:27-06:00", "id": 219366, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1310807, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 16384, "username": "774772", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I was having the same problem.  After 6 attempts this week, I tried it without moving my character at all.  I just let him punt me around without repositioning him, and he didn't despawn this time.  Try it out and see if it works for you, or if it was just a fluke.", "creationdate": "2011-01-28T09:59:09-06:00", "id": 219659, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1310807, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "drothar", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 73, "id": 1313132, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Nobbel", "body": "Easy to solo in Cataclysm:\nhttp://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fYZTnSkDuLs\n\nFor me the despawning happend during his knockback. I think it has something to do with not hitting him for a moment. Saved my avengers shield to make sure to atleast get a hit on him. Not sure if this is what got him down or if it's just luck.", "date": "2011-01-28T10:49:58-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 384, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-01-28T10:52:31-06:00", 1, "Nobbel"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 74, "id": 1313344, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "17100", "body": "[b]Magtheridon is even more managable at level 85\r\n Did it 2man (balance druid & blood death knight) both with item level ~346.[/b]\r\n\r\nThe only real trouble was killing the channelers because of their heals. We had them grouped up, but focused on one at a time - we couldn't prevent all the heals though.\r\n\r\nI didn't see the death knight drop lower than 95% health because of his selfheals. In theory a blood death knight could probably solo this, if he manage to get the adds down himself. As a balance druid I didn't have to heal him, and only had to worry about dealing damage.\r\n\r\nHe dropped ~492 gold, which is a fairly good payment for 15 minutes of work.", "date": "2011-01-28T14:21:52-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 75, "id": 1316091, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Karoxen", "body": "Okay. One thing that's always bugged me about this guy. He has a giant-ass spear on him.\r\n\r\nNow somehow along the way of Illidan beating this guy up and hauling his ass to Hellfire Citadel and keeping him under lock, it NEVER occured to him to take away his spear.", "date": "2011-01-30T17:30:18-06:00", "rating": 16, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Illidan's just too awesome to worry about a simple spear.", "creationdate": "2011-04-16T02:27:12-05:00", "id": 238063, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1316091, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Kasa24", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "No, that's obviously not it. Illidan [i]did[/i] take away his spear, but in true [b]Mag-guyver[/b] style (see what I did there?) he fashioned a new spear from a piece of pipe from behind the toilet, a couple of his own teeth, and shards of broken rock from the ceiling.  Now THAT is pro weapon-making.", "creationdate": "2011-07-09T03:32:53-05:00", "id": 251199, "rating": 3, "commentid": 1316091, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Quandru", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 76, "id": 1319957, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "572609", "body": "Soloed by paladin in Cataclysm..\r\n\r\nhttp://www.youtube.com/watch?v=S2ei7dyi4nE\r\n\r\n\"Magtheridon vs Neka\u00e9l\"", "date": "2011-02-03T00:54:41-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 77, "id": 1319967, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Tekunin", "body": "Just solo'd this guy as an 85 MM Hunter (7/31/3) with a Turtle as my pet;  Currently 330 ilvl.\r\n\r\nMake sure you clear all the trash;  I thought I was clever and Camouflage'd past the trash packs, and of course when I pulled they all aggro'd.\r\n\r\nI didn't bother killing the five adds at the due to their healing each other constantly;  Instead I let my turtle tank them as well as Magtheridon once he engaged.  My turtle couldn't pick up all the Infernals that kept spawning, so I ended up kiting them around a circle while DPS'ing in Aspect of the Fox and kept my turtle in the middle of the room about where Magtheridon is when you walk in.  \r\n\r\nI was able to keep the Infernals off of me mostly with running/DPSing in Aspect of the Fox alone as they run slower than I do, but I dropped Frost Traps every now and then for some extra distance since Magtheridon's earthquakes make it easy for them to catch up.  In the end the healing from Chimera Shot heavily outweighted any Shadow Bolt Volley/Blast Wave/Infernal Damage.\r\n\r\nI'm not sure about how long it took me to kill him, but I didn't hit his enrage timer so you can assume it was in a time span shorter than that :P", "date": "2011-02-03T01:17:33-06:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "By 350 iLevel, a MM hunter should have no problem with him no matter what type of pet they have out. Have your pet attack the first add, and it's not a bad idea to misdirect at least one Multi-shot once they are all together. Pick one from the four your pet isn't on, and peel it off. Alone, they die fairly easily, just be ready to hit Silencing Shot when they get below 50%.  Repeat the process to keep killing the orcs, keeping in mind your healing from Chimera Shot and Spirit Bond will generate threat so MDing another Multi-shot or two between each add to keep the others on your pet is not a b", "creationdate": "2011-02-03T01:17:34-06:00", "id": 479417, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1319967, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Manae", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "As a MM hunter i did this with my Crab pet and a normal 3/33/5 talent tree (without silencing shot) several times now. I use the mend pet glyph to help heal.  The trick is to place all offensive traps just in front of where you think the caster will step onto when the crab goes to tank it, pop rapid killing, chimera shot, readiness, chimera shot again and when rapid killing falls off you just pop it again (this should be done with your trinkets if they are on-use trinkets). The extra dmg from the traps helps to finish off the first caster rather fast.  When you have killed one caster the rest ", "creationdate": "2011-02-03T01:17:34-06:00", "id": 482368, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1319967, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Gilgamesh83", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 78, "id": 1321291, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Nobbel", "body": "New better version of how to solo Magtheridon:\r\nhttp://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4TOkTZokCPc\r\n\r\n500gold, epic gems, a bag and a few items in 15 to 30 mins.", "date": "2011-02-04T07:29:48-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 384, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 79, "id": 1326529, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "citrique", "body": "Amusingly, while this boss was rather easily soloable by a DK at 80 in tank gear towards the end of tier 10, this boss is now soloable by a DK at 85 in DPS gear / frost spec. Just burn the adds down one at a time at the start, ignore the infernals, then burn mag down. Howling blast spam on the adds is nice because their heals are \"dumb\" in that they will all heal the lowest HP target, so just AOEing and focusing one add, then switching to one of the others and bursting after all of them overheal the low one will make getting them down easy.\n\nThe advantage of doing it as frost, of course, is time savings. Instead of it taking me 15 minutes, it took me about 5.\n\nI did it in mostly 359 gear with a few 372 pieces and my HP didn't dip below 50% after the adds were all dead. The new dark succor glyph coming in tomorrow's patch should make this even more trivial.", "date": "2011-02-08T05:08:10-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-02-08T05:09:27-06:00", 1, "citrique"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 80, "id": 1330839, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "678942", "body": "Just soloed this guy as combat rogue. Used normal pve spec and had full epic gear. Just burned channelers down and tried interrupt the heal as much i could. When I had killed all channelers I was pretty low but Magtheridn doesn't hit very hard so i could out heal him with recuperate.", "date": "2011-02-10T18:04:16-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Did you still get infernals alone? they were a big issue for my group of 3 last weekend.  1 Prot pally 1 Ret pally 1 Warrior  We owned the trash but it was a bit harder to keep ourselves up during the fight as more infernals seemed to come from all directions, Magtheridon himself doesnt hit very hard and isnt too hard to take down.", "creationdate": "2011-02-10T18:36:05-06:00", "id": 478099, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1330839, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Randoom", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Yeah, just evasion tanked them and burned channelers down as fast as possible.", "creationdate": "2011-02-11T05:38:16-06:00", "id": 478145, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1330839, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "678942", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 81, "id": 1331042, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Arbron", "body": "Soloable by prot warrior with ~150k health unbuffed.\r\n\r\nYou can't proc Impending Victory from the adds reliably because of their healing. There really isn't a lot of strategy to this fight, just try to Shockwave the adds (to stun the abyssals) every time it's ready and always keep them in front of you.\r\n\r\n10 minute fight, during which I took about 950k damage total. Only a third of that was from Magtheridon himself. I did about 970k healing, the vast majority of which was Blood Craze (550k), then Mending enchant (200k).", "date": "2011-02-10T21:18:35-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 82, "id": 1331853, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Nubia", "body": "Soloed pretty easily as a Retribution Paladin using Seal of Insight,Blessing of Kings,and Resistance Aura in a mix of 333-359 gear,standard PvE spec.\r\n\r\nThe fight is incredibly simple,and never changes from 100% to 0%.Bunch all the adds and Magtheridon together,and spam Divine Storm (I've not used Crusader Strike on this fight once) along with Word of Glory whenever Divine Purpose comes up,use Offensive CDs as much as possible to shorten the fight.In my experience,the combined heals from those two abilities+Seal of Insight have been enough to keep me above 40% health through the entire fight.\r\n\r\nAdditional tips: \r\n-The Channelers will most likely not die throughout the encounter,this is fine since it helps with Divine Storm heals. \r\n-Magtheridon [b]seems [/b]to not despawn if you never move and just let him throw you around the room.\r\n-Blast Nova is a non-issue,you can just continue the fight normally through it. (Lamenting that a once raid destroying move can be completely ignored by a single person is entirely acceptable)", "date": "2011-02-11T12:43:31-06:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 83, "id": 1341063, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "784207", "body": "Soloed today on my 85 blood dk in a mix of reg/heroic 5 man gear.  took me 15 mins.  didnt kill any adds, just stayed on mags at the door the entire time. very easy, health didnt go below 20%.", "date": "2011-02-18T13:30:21-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 84, "id": 1341659, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Morbius", "body": "I can safely say that the glitch is caused by getting knocked towards the wall by earthquake. I soloed him today with my DK but it took me 2 tries. The first try reset after I got knocked towards the wall by earthquake. The second try I tanked him in the middle and downed him easily. That earthquake is so annoying. I did it with blood spec in unholy presence for the extra healing from glyph of dark succor.", "date": "2011-02-19T00:12:36-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-02-19T00:13:07-06:00", 1, "Morbius"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 85, "id": 1342148, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "ScumHellfire", "body": "Done with 10 level 70's (well 9, one of our healers disconnected).\r\n\r\nMake sure to keep the channelers away from eachother so they don't heal. And put one interrupter on each mob, interrupting only Dark Mending. Shadowball Volley can be healed through. The fight itself was easy, we didn't even have to use the cubes anymore.", "date": "2011-02-19T11:34:37-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 86, "id": 1342785, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Butch82", "body": "Easily soloed as a Fury Warrior. Just use Recklessness/Death Whish to nuke down the Channelers asap, pummel their heal as often as you can and ignore the elementals. Once all the Channelers are down, use Enraged Regeneration. For the next 3 min use Bloodthirst (with Glyph of Bloody Healing) on every cooldown to keep yourself up and slowly dps him down. Use Enraged Regeneration again and finish him off.\n\nThe fight took about 6 min including adds. 4.5m damage done, 477k damage taken, 451k healing done(265k Bloodthirst, 186k Enraged Regeneration).", "date": "2011-02-19T22:24:21-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-02-19T22:54:11-06:00", 2, "Butch82"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 87, "id": 1343790, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "lithoe", "body": "When soloing him, he likes to despawn while throwing you around. Therefore tank him sticking to the wall and enjoy your loot.", "date": "2011-02-20T17:32:38-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 88, "id": 1343843, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "671464", "body": "Enurtal Doomhammer prot pala!\r\nJust soloed this dude! took me 3 attempts and 30 mins but i nailed him!\r\nWell worth it he dropped near enough 520g and around 50-80g in vendor stuff\r\nWell worth it :) this is my new weekly activity", "date": "2011-02-20T18:15:57-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 89, "id": 1346774, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Morbius", "body": "This fight is so buggy. He reset on me twice before I killed him. I think I know what's going on. If you get knocked away from him while he's busy doing something, like blast nova or making the ceiling cave in, he'll reset. The first time he reset when I got knocked back just as he did the emote for the cave in. The second time he reset when I got knocked back while he was doing blast nova. So basically try to keep aggro on him with dots or ranged attacks.", "date": "2011-02-23T03:22:30-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Same has happened to me right now with my dk.  It's really strange, because it never happened before.", "creationdate": "2011-02-23T11:40:08-06:00", "id": 227674, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1346774, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "xzbbzx", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 90, "id": 1348817, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "LifeFeel", "body": "Last night I was very mad because of Magtheridon disappearing 5 times in a row - I lost an hour and about 60 gold for repairs. I wrote a ticket. Here is the GM response:\r\n\r\nGame Master (GM) Response:\r\n\r\nWhat you report normally happens when Magtheridon is either being soloed or the party facing him has very small numbers (less than 4). We have reported the issue to the development team, but the fact is the magtheridon encounter is a raid encounter and was designed having a raid in mind and not a small party, and because of that they are not very tempted to alter the encounter.\r\n\r\nAs such the only advise we can offer is to not try to solo magtheridon and build a small party.", "date": "2011-02-24T17:17:31-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "What the GM told you is a lie. This had never happened before this patch.  If anything, they addressed the issue so that it could not be soloed, but it's not an error that's been there for a long time without being addressed.", "creationdate": "2011-02-25T05:07:33-06:00", "id": 479762, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1348817, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "xzbbzx", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 91, "id": 1350267, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "575688", "body": "Perfectly soloable as prot war with  346 gear\r\nno need to bring down anything .\r\nyust keep debuffs up on all adds and infernals while you wait for  boss to be set free..\r\n\r\nthen grab him and rotate Cooldowns when he does his blast nova\r\n\r\nEnraged regeneration  back up from 50% and repeat \r\n\r\nnot much of a challange\r\nexept for the fact he keeps despawning now and then and it gets annoying\r\nbut perfectly soloable by all tank classes and most dps classes\r\n\r\nGood Luck", "date": "2011-02-26T00:03:05-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 92, "id": 1350349, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "warmblanket", "body": "feral druids", "date": "2011-02-26T02:13:09-06:00", "rating": -2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-02-26T12:10:35-06:00", 1, "warmblanket"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 93, "id": 1350571, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Teevo", "body": "I too was able to solo him at 85 with 346iLevel gear. MM spec. Used my Terrorpene to tank the adds. His shell shield + cower is nice when you realize you stopped paying attention to his hp for a few, as theres a decent amount going on that you need to focus on.\n\nTook a few attempts to get the hang of what to do, and which method seemed to work for me. I ended up finding it much easier to do the not killing the adds method. Key points taken from above plus some of my own:\n\n- use Aspect of the Fox\n- Chimera Shot as often as you can; the heal from it will keep you alive\n- Misdirect your pet alot (just worry about misdirecting Mags, dont have to worry about multi-shotting the adds once Mags is free); I highly suggest using Glyph of Misdirection\n- lay frost traps for the infernals and just kite them back and forth across the room\n- have your pet tank the adds/Mag somewhere near the wall; stay at max range so you dont get hit by the caster's shadowbolt volley\n- keep an eye on your pet; he can spike from time to time; use an occassional mend pet (dont need to spam it, just once in a while); and like I said earlier, use cower/shell shield every CD\n- make sure you have thunderstomp on auto, it will keep aggro on the caster adds while he is targeting Mag with growl\n- I spec'ed into Spirit Bond 2/2; proved helpful since you dont have time to bandage\n\nHope this info helps.\n\nEdit: Btw.. he dropped 483g, not an even 500  ;)  Not sure if that changes each kill or not. I would suspect not.", "date": "2011-02-26T07:37:42-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-02-26T07:43:40-06:00", 1, "Teevo"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 94, "id": 1352973, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "clavarnway", "body": "Just solo'd as a Destruction Warlock.  The trick is to use [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=77801]Demon Soul: Voidwalker[/url] to put threat on all the [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=17256]channelers[/url] onto your [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=697]Voidwalker[/url].  Then use the Move To command to park your Voidwalker in place, and 1 at a time peel the Channelers off your pet and pull them out of heal range.  Then kill them one at a time.  Then pick up [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=17257]Magtheridon[/url] once he pops.", "date": "2011-02-28T09:22:24-06:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Did this tonight with a holy priest trying your method and it worked well.  I'm going to try it next week alone.  BTW, this was my first time doing this raid ever.", "creationdate": "2011-03-04T05:52:31-06:00", "id": 229902, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1352973, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "768305", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 95, "id": 1353735, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "kabookiejoe", "body": "in the up coming patch, raids such as karazhan, mag etc will have there gold values reduce by quite some bit according to the latest patch notes", "date": "2011-03-01T02:33:57-06:00", "rating": 10, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 96, "id": 1365506, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "740032", "body": "Blood DK -\r\n\r\nDidn't even bother with adds, death striked/rune tap to keep HP topped off\r\n\r\nWhen Mag breaks free,\r\n\r\nStand against wall/in corner, Death strike every time its available, keep diseases up/army/raise dead to keep max dps so it doesn't take too long\r\n\r\nTook me about 9 minutes from the time i first pulled channelers.\r\n\r\nlvl 85 Blood DK 349 ilvl avg", "date": "2011-03-13T03:54:29-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 97, "id": 1366771, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "498890", "body": "Stupidly easy as an 85 prot pally, just ignore the adds and back to a wall so he doesn't reset.", "date": "2011-03-14T12:45:07-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 98, "id": 1366899, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Kptch", "body": "If you are going to solo this boss, I suggest just disregarding the adds because you likely can't kill any of them. Focus on staying at full health during the first phase and then start rotating your cooldowns when p2 starts.\r\n\r\nMagtheridon will also reset if you move too much out of his attack range, for instance during the earthquake, so you should tank him with your back against a corner (not at the doorway though or you'll again risk resets).", "date": "2011-03-14T15:27:16-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 99, "id": 1373956, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "KodiackOfThrall", "body": "I have soloed this on my Marksmanship hunter twice now. I have a level 84 bear tanking for me, and I have managed to take the adds out to really simplify the fight. As there's a rather long timer between engaging the encounter and Magtheridon becoming active, you have a lot of time to do stuff. The trick is to MD all of it to your pet except for one. You'll want to aggro one of the adds and kite it using Aspect of the Fox. When it's far enough away from the rest of the channelers, you'll find that that add will [i]only[/i] be healed by itself. You can easily burst damage through this or use silencing shut to interrupt the cast. Either way, you can take one out every few dozen seconds or so. \r\n\r\nYou'll also find that the encounter becomes exponentially easier when you knock 2-3 adds. The rest of the adds will have less channelers to heal them, the burning abyssal count will drop down, and damage to your and your pet will also fall. Magtheridon's easy enough with just one or two alive, but if that's all you have left you might as well burst through them.\r\n\r\nBy the by, I also use the hunter 2-piece T5 set bonus, causing my pet to be healed for 15% of the damage I do. This - combined with pet talent heals and Blood of the Rhino - makes for an exceptionally trivial encounter. My main problem was keeping the abyssals' aggro on my bear; this was easily solved with misdirects and finely-timed feign deaths, though.", "date": "2011-03-23T03:19:49-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 100, "id": 1374582, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "MazzaTheFirst", "body": "Just did it as a BM hunter, around 350 iLevel in PvP gear (Enchanted and gemed). Used a Tenacity pet (worm) to tank all the channelers in the middle with Magtheridon. Was in Aspect of the Fox and just circle strafed to outrun the infernals. Was a really easy fight as Spirit Bond out healed all Blast Novas and Mend Pet healed a lot higher then they could damage. Just nuked down Magtheridon and ignored the channelers.", "date": "2011-03-23T22:43:40-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 101, "id": 1374598, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "583323", "body": "It cannot be understated how easy this is for a level 85 prot pally.  I hit 85, forgot to train Guardian of Ancient Kings (but I put my talent point in!) and took off for Outland in quest greens, 316 dungeon blues, and a couple pieces of rep-based 333's (Ishmerai on Silvermoon, FYI).  I used short cooldowns pretty regularly to mitigate things like blast nova and not to get caught by the enrage timer.  It took me 17 minutes from starting the fight, and I was being conservative with holy power, opting for heals over damage to keep myself topped off.\r\n\r\nSeriously, start farming this before they reduce the gold dropped.", "date": "2011-03-23T23:03:19-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 102, "id": 1376343, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "235468", "body": "I just tried soloing this guy as a shadow priest... not going to happen. I'm poorly geared (heroic level stuff) but I really don't think raid epics will make a difference.\r\n\r\nI wasn't specced into Silence, so my only real way of surviving into Phase 2 was to put on Inner Will and run in circles around Magtheridon. Make sure to put Shadow Word: Pain on one of the channellers around every 8 seconds, or they'll \"leash\" and despawn, resetting the encounter.\r\n\r\nOnce Magtheridon was unleashed, things got ugly. Really ugly. I was able to take down 3% of his health before he started up with an earthquake which put an end to my kiting. Even if that didn't happen, he probably would have reset anyways.\r\n\r\nMy usual trick when I'm overwhelmed in solo raid encounters is to summon my shadow fiend and use Fade. That didn't seem to work here. I'm not sure if it's my 9% chance to miss or it just not working on some bosses.\r\n\r\nIf some more skilled or significantly more geared shadow priests want to build off of my probably misguided strategy, feel free.", "date": "2011-03-26T02:04:59-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I had tried it on my priest as shadow with similar results.  Vampiric Embrace just didn't beat all the damage I was taking.  Your best bet is to find another person with a class that can't solo it and just 2-man it.  I went holy and healed my wife on her 84 mage.  We had one silly wipe, but then we had no trouble at all on the second attempt.  As I get better gear, I'm probably crazy enough to keep trying on my shadow priest, but it takes skill beyond mine.  There's no shame in splitting the gold with someone else who's going to have a hard time soloing.", "creationdate": "2011-03-28T16:06:32-05:00", "id": 234890, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1376343, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "583323", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 103, "id": 1379865, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Anarchy", "body": "Solo'd as a fury warrior.\r\nA tough and close fight, came within an inch of my life, I was on 6k hp at one point, one more cleave and I was gone.\r\n\r\nTactic is to blow your CDs to kill the channelers fast or you'll waste precious health and time because they can outheal you.\r\n\r\nThen of course start on maggy, use demoralizing shout so he hits less hard and sunder armor for as much damage as possible.\r\n\r\nPop enraged regen when you're at 40% or 50% HP, you'll want to use it sooner than later because you're going to need to use it again near the end.\r\n\r\nHP is key to this fight, use anything you can to keep your health high, more HP = more healing from bloodthirst and enraged regen.\r\n\r\nUse a macro for shield wall and shield block to survive a bit longer until your enraged regen cooldown resets.\r\n\r\n/equiptset shields\r\n/cast defensive stance\r\n/cast shield wall\r\n/cast shield block", "date": "2011-03-30T07:59:36-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 104, "id": 1388156, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Exias", "body": "I soloed this as a Protection Paladin with an average item level of 350. It was quite a long fight. Things to note:\r\n\r\n[ul]\r\n[li]For the trash, one group at a time should be pulled; the trash uses Death Coil (fear). The mobs themselves aren't hard despite being ? level; however, the fear makes it hard to heal. I had to use Lay on Hands when fear caused me to aggro a second group and I wasn't able to heal through the fears fast enough.[/li]\r\n[li]The channelers should be fought until Magtheridon engages you. Then they can be ignored. There's no way to kill them since they heal each other.[/li]\r\n[li]You want to be on the defensive or alternating between defensive and offensive (e.g., swapping between Seal of Insight and Seal of Corruption as well as Word of Glory and Inquisition) since the mobs are strong enough to kill you unless you're constantly healing yourself.[/li]\r\n[li]Do not put your back to the door. When he uses his knockback, being knocked into the door can cause the fight to reset. (The boss and friends will vanish and reappear in a few moments.)[/li]\r\n[li]After the boss dies, the channelers and their pets will still be attacking you, so make sure that your health isn't too low. I almost got killed when I decided to go all offense at the end and had low health as a result; I ended up bubbling and spamming Flash Heal.[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\n\r\nI was a bit amused at the end; I used Nitro Boosts to escape the channelers, the belt tinker malfunctioned, and I was ejected onto the floor above Magtheridon's Lair. That platform happens to be the platform that the final boss stands on in The Blood Furnace instance. The door leading out of that area is just a blue wall though; walking through it will drop you back into the original dungeon and cause you to take more than 50% of your health in fall damage. The malfunction ultimately ended up being kind of helpful because it caused the channelers to vanish.", "date": "2011-04-10T06:08:33-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 105, "id": 1391112, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "sk8r2000", "body": "Just solo'd as a Blood Death Knight at level 85, ilvl 349. It was a pretty tough fight; here's how I did it.\r\n\r\nFirst off, every time you pull a trash group, take it near to the entrance (except for your final one). This ensures that you won't be feared into anything, and that you won't pull the patrol if it's still up. Once every group has been taken out, go down to Magtheridon and aggro the channelers. You won't be able to dps through the heals unless you're incredibly good at interrupting the heals, so just focus on dpsing it until Magtheridon comes out. \r\n\r\nGet Mag as soon as you can and just start dpsing him down. Make sure that you put diseases on all of the adds with Pestilence, and also try to do some AOE moves. After this, it's pretty much a case of self-healing with Blood Strike and Rune Tap until he goes down. Loot your stuff quickly and run out before the adds take you down.", "date": "2011-04-14T10:10:50-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 106, "id": 1392339, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Kasa24", "body": "Anyone having trouble with Mag despawning, one solution is to simply not move. On the Magtheridon's Lair page, someone contacted a GM about it and he said the problem is because the raid isn't meant to be solo'd with just a few people.\n\nJust solo'd him my first time today, and I just stood in the same spot - had no trouble at all.\n\nAgreeing with all the posts above me, simple and easy to farm. Ret pally in mostly blue gear, some BOE epics (Ilvl344), just keep hitting Divine Storm every time it's on CD and you'll have it made. \n\nOccasionally pop in a Word of Glory or Holy Radiance and you'll never go below 50%. I also used Seal of Insight for the fight. Also, you may want to make sure that your gear is fully repaired. You'll be getting hit a LOT during this fight as melee DPS, and you want to make sure your gear will last the entire fight.\n\nEdit: Typos.", "date": "2011-04-16T02:54:52-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-04-16T02:58:33-05:00", 2, "Kasa24"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 107, "id": 1393767, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Haphasto", "body": "Just tried soloing ol' Mag literally a few minutes ago as a Goblin Death Knight, and I just couldn't do it, do to the enrage timer.  This is where being a Blood Elf is key, because of their aoe silence.  I could not keep the adds from healing each other, and it took a tremendous amount of time to kill them, coupled with some lucky kill shots.  \r\n\r\nI went into this with my raid spec, which is not hit or expertise capped, and I'm also missing a few abilities that would increase my damage a little bit by sacrificing a little evasion.  I had absolutely no trouble keeping myself alive through this fight, so the sacrifice could definitely be made.  I did a majority of the fight in Frost Presence, but it was only when I switched to Unholy Presence was I able to start downing the adds, do to faster rune regeneration.  By the time Magtheridon enraged, I had him at 60%.  *sigh", "date": "2011-04-17T19:05:33-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 108, "id": 1393858, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Superchief", "body": "To all Blood Death Knights - yeah roger, we understand you have been overpowered since the launch of cataclysm and can solo everything up to and including the Lich King and it's been proven. We don't need anymore \"har har laughably soloable by a blood DK\" posts. Thanks. Frustrated prot warrior here.", "date": "2011-04-17T23:11:57-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 109, "id": 1394037, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Iroared", "body": "Should be soloable by any class with decent self healing. Unless you're a tank, you can kill the adds before mag activates: bring two to around 65% simultaneously, then hit one, wait for everyone to start casting a heal, pop cds and burn the other one. While CDs are up you should be able to kill 1 or 2 more, then its more or less a cake; when CDs are down just interrupt the heals.", "date": "2011-04-18T06:04:54-05:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 110, "id": 1394269, "nreplies": 7, "sticky": 0, "user": "Arrei", "body": "In light of the upcoming gold nerf, does anyone know what his new gold drops are on the 4.1 PTR? My guess is something like 10% of what he used to drop..", "date": "2011-04-18T14:32:38-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "according to [url=http://www.myrddin.de/patch-4-1-introduces-massive-drop-in-gold-from-certain-bosses/]this guy[/url] it will indeed be a 90% nerf.  Same source mentiones that the fight itself will be nerfed too (channelers no longer help each other). This is gonna make the fight even more ridiculously easy than it used to be. [edit: seems that was a ptr bug or something they experimented with for a while or so, however after 4.1 hit live the channelers behave as they always did. You aggro one you aggro all.]  To be honest, 50 gold for 7 minutes of tank and spank seems more approbriate than 50", "creationdate": "2011-04-18T14:32:39-05:00", "id": 484233, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1394269, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "662504", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I doubt it'll be 10%.  That would be around 50g, which is what the Kara bosses drop, and they're nerfing the gold drops there too (why, I have no idea-since when is 50g a lot in Cata? You get more from a random dungeon than a Kara boss).", "creationdate": "2011-04-22T15:27:36-05:00", "id": 484068, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1394269, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Firebyrd", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Confirmed at 10% of what he used to drop. Just solo'd him patch 4.1 on live server. He dropped 47 gold. They have effectively removed Magtheridon from the game. There is absolutely no reason to go there now.", "creationdate": "2011-04-26T23:19:21-05:00", "id": 484317, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1394269, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "804945", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Just soloed Magtheridon in live 4.1 server. Money loot was nerfed to 50g 18c.  It's not worth doing anymore for the money.", "creationdate": "2011-04-27T06:46:50-05:00", "id": 240025, "rating": 4, "commentid": 1394269, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "corn", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Just soloed it and the Channellers healed eachother. Gold drop has indeed been nerfed by about 90%, I got 51 gold and some change in pure gold drops. Along with other drops I netted about 75 gold after vendoring everything.", "creationdate": "2011-05-01T05:27:21-05:00", "id": 241008, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1394269, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Delaios", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 111, "id": 1394423, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "gtadem", "body": "I've solo'ed Mag before. The last six times I've tried though, he despawns. I've tried keeping him as close to center of room as possible. I've tried making sure I use ranged to keep his interest in me when I'm being knocked back. I can't seem to avoid it. It always happens during or immediately after being bounced around. So I was thinking I could use Divine Shield to stop one set from tossing me about. Does anybody know if Hand of Protection or Hand of Freedom would similarly save me?", "date": "2011-04-18T19:25:52-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 112, "id": 1400615, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "816837", "body": "Update for people who are terrible at soloing like me : in spite of the rumours, the channelers still heal each other as of 4.1\n\nDownrate facts. GG.", "date": "2011-04-26T23:37:19-05:00", "rating": 60, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "The facts have a clear anti-soloing bias.", "creationdate": "2011-12-14T17:23:47-06:00", "id": 496991, "rating": 5, "commentid": 1400615, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "gazmik", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "We tried a guildrun tonight. As soon as I charged the channeler, the gate shut down, and I had to solo him, while 9 guild members was nagging outside :/", "creationdate": "2012-04-06T15:24:54-05:00", "id": 533555, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1400615, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "838725", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Just have to be able to burst them.", "creationdate": "2012-12-27T15:00:59-06:00", "id": 616353, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1400615, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "RiftWalker", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-05-04T02:53:12-05:00", 1, "816837"]}
