{"commentv2": 1, "number": 115, "id": 1406551, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Shogol", "body": "Why do DKs say this was a tough fight? In my 350 ilvl dps gear I solo this with my eyes closed, its so easy of course not worth oding anymore but you just let the adds pound away on you while you dps magtheridon you must be doing something horribly wrong, just spam death strike and you will barely take damage (blood shield) will absorb almost everything.", "date": "2011-05-01T17:33:04-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 116, "id": 1407160, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Khronix", "body": "I'm a blood elf death knight and I've tried killing mag in blood spec and I can't understand how you kill the 5 adds at the start of the fight because the heal each other... my racial (Arcane Torrent) doesn't help... I've also tried blood and unholy presence.\r\n\r\nTo heal myself I've been spamming death strikes and keeping up diseases but it doesn't heal me enough after they start spawning their demons", "date": "2011-05-02T10:05:57-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "To explain how you kill them..... You don't. As a blood dk in tank gear, your Ds and the ocasional Heal-cd-combo from the proc is enough to let them pound on you, no sweat.", "creationdate": "2011-05-02T14:42:15-05:00", "id": 241381, "rating": 4, "commentid": 1407160, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "643018", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 117, "id": 1422033, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "829563", "body": "Just did it as bear, tried to kill adds, just not enough dps, so I ended up tanking them all, and killing Mag's. I might have got down to 50% hp at the lowest, ended the fight around 80%.  So easy for tanks.\r\n\r\nDropped 48g 87s 87c.", "date": "2011-05-18T20:53:14-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 118, "id": 1423962, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Blankadin", "body": "Gold drops for this mob have been significantly reduced.\nDropped 59g exact for me.\n\nAlso, as for how to do it on an 85 hunter solo:\n\nUse turtle pet. I specced for Thunderstomp, but your mileage may vary.\nGet 2 channelers low HP, push one, then swap targets and kill it.\nRepeat until at least 2 channelers are down.\nTrap one Infernal, kite the remainder.\nIf you get low, feign after the next Blast Wave (unless its >12 secs) and bandage.\nAfter Mag goes down, dismiss pet and feign to despawn channelers.\n\nI did it as a PvE surv, nothing special about it, only had Mend Pet glyph.", "date": "2011-05-21T13:50:48-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-05-21T13:56:54-05:00", 1, "Blankadin"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 119, "id": 1437076, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Volviga", "body": "Easily soloable as a Demo Lock -ilvl 352 for that matter- , burn down the adds with Meta and Felstorm and you will have 20+ seconds left in Meta when Magtheridon aggros. Stay at the 40 yard range, let Felguard pound on Mag and just unload everything you have on him. \n\nFor some reason Boss-lvl-mobs don't react fast on heavy damage when you stand on the 40 yards range, so you can burn it down fairly easy.\n\n50g drop + g from the items gave me 125g, still a nice amount :)", "date": "2011-06-08T13:23:51-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Confirming that this is pretty comfortable to solo as a Demonology warlock at 85. Just stacking up the 5 adds, and dropping Metamorphosis, Immolation Aura, Hellfire, Felstorm tends to get them all down pretty damn quickly - and once the 5 adds are down, it's a free kill. He really does hit like a wet kitten and you can easily tank him with your Felguard with only occasional heals necessary.   Don't be discouraged if the first phase goes horribly wrong - if you get unlucky with AOE crits, you can sometimes find that a couple of them reach the health percentage that triggers them to start healin", "creationdate": "2011-06-08T13:23:52-05:00", "id": 486986, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1437076, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "vaderas", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Your wet kitten hits pretty strong. ;)", "creationdate": "2012-03-16T13:10:31-05:00", "id": 527717, "rating": -1, "commentid": 1437076, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "lyom", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-06-08T13:27:07-05:00", 1, "Volviga"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 120, "id": 1440896, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "paladine20", "body": "Can anyone confirm Mag disappearing roughly 5 minutes into the fight?", "date": "2011-06-13T19:03:06-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Yes it does happen when you're being bounced around. Try fighting him with your back against a wall, it should not happen again.", "creationdate": "2011-07-05T07:04:20-05:00", "id": 250252, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1440896, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "JTN83", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 121, "id": 1495391, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Rederoin", "body": "For those trying to solo him as a hunter(at 85). \r\nI was in PvP-gear(4 piece vicious, 2 pieces of bloodthirsty,  rest  333/334Ivl PvE blue's)\r\n\r\n\r\nI used a different approach than the hunter above me,  I did however use a turtle pet.\r\nGet your turtle(or tenacity) pet to aggro all the caster,  do the same with the adds that get spawned.\r\nUse misdirect to keep them all on your pet(Multishot helps). If the adds won't aggro your pet during the encounter for same reason, use multi-shot and aspect of the fox to kite them. While attacking the boss.   Besides all that, its a fairly simple encounter. Just make sure you heal your pet and use his CD's.", "date": "2011-08-15T06:31:45-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 122, "id": 1498206, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Deviruchi13", "body": "Just soloed him, he droped 50g + itens that i sold for another 50g, so aproximately 100G per week by soloing this guy, not that worth it.", "date": "2011-08-19T00:31:23-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 123, "id": 1505335, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "never00", "body": "A quick note:\r\n85 warrior:  solo, clear, no quests, takes about 28 minutes on Heroic\r\n2900 rep with Honor Hold\r\n60g from mobs\r\n29g from selling junk\r\n10 random greens\r\n3 stacks of netherweave\r\n\r\nThe room at the bottom of the path before you go to the final boss is a pain.  Lots of knockback and other attacks that prevent you from doing damage.  It is possible to die there if you pull the room.", "date": "2011-08-28T12:14:25-05:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This guy is talking about blood furnace from what I gathered.", "creationdate": "2011-09-07T03:04:32-05:00", "id": 491114, "rating": 3, "commentid": 1505335, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "minimagikman", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 124, "id": 1513153, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "323845", "body": "i killed that now and he drops  49 g 81 s 46 c", "date": "2011-09-08T15:08:38-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 125, "id": 1514260, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Pyratewench", "body": "Downed him with 4 people..none of us knew what to do (all newer players-yaya solo all you want but we are newbs...we run in packs), so thought we'd give it a go with us guildies who were on and not busy.\r\n\r\n85 retadin, 85 arms, 71 healadin (she dps'd till I died, then took over healing), and me...68 restodrood. wiped first try as we didn't realize just how well those castors were healing each other till 2mins up and Mag started wailing on us while we're still trying add control. Read up strat on wowhead, ran back in for 2nd try.\r\n\r\nI died very quickly as I was um...not paying attention to healing myself but instead was tossing FF on the castors (which we did lucky charm this time around and focus burned them), and picked up too much aggro. I stayed dead for the rest of the fight to call out directions....seemed better that way.\r\n\r\nBurned castors one by one with only 1 left when Mag engaged, then pretty much they just ignored the last castor and burned Mag. He went down no problem and worst damage taken was the other heals getting hit by some falling rocks at same time as the Blast Nova.\r\n\r\nSloppy...but first time our guild tried something other than a quick run through MC (85 pally running me through for gear XD) or normal 5mans, so was nice for the new experience. :)", "date": "2011-09-09T23:27:45-05:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 126, "id": 1522238, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "wvance", "body": "Soloable as an 85 AA/A specced discipline priest.  ~360 iLvl.   \n\nIntellect: 5948\nSpirit:  2426\nHaste:  10.92%\nCrit:  14.65%\nMastery: 11.70\n\n\n[url=http://www.wowhead.com/talent#bfGorRsbcorochM:qVmdqazM0]33/8/0[/url] - I went with Focused Will & Inspiration for the extra damage reduction.\n\nI never could get the knack of killing the channelers as Shadow, so I just switched to discipline and tanked the adds while focusing on Mag.  It took me about [b]13 m 30s[/b]  to down Mag once he became active.\n\n[ul]\n[li]HF/Smite (kind of obvious)[/li]\n[li]Use PW: Shield on CD for absorb and rapture[/li]\n[li]Use PoM and Renew after Penance to take advantage of Grace buff [/li]\n[li]Don't forget to use Archangel Evangelism on CD [/li]\n[li]Back against a wall to minimize the chance of despawn[/li]\n[li]Don't be afraid to use your cooldowns since it's going to be a long fight.[/li]\n[/ul]\n\nHappy hunting!\n\nEdit: spelling typo", "date": "2011-09-19T23:19:44-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-02-27T09:15:48-06:00", 1, "wvance"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 127, "id": 1568324, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Jdekik", "body": "Confirm Mag disappeared several times when soloing it plus 3 lags and 2 disconnections, was getting annoying when down him to 100k of hp then restarting the encounter because of that, I managed to get behind the Hellfire channeler on the left just entering the room then tank'd all HCs while dpsing Magtheridon.\r\n\r\nAs feral tank I downed the HC's when the one I have focused was low on hp, I pop'd Berserker - Berserking << (Troll's racial) - Lifeblood << (herbalism spell) then skull bashed all Dark mendings then when those 3 on cd was using ff if wasn't up, Lacerate, Thrash, Mangle, Swipe and Maul.", "date": "2011-11-10T01:31:33-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 128, "id": 1570819, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Taraezor", "body": "Just spelling out a few things for anyone new to soloing Mags...\n\n1) Around the perimeter of his lair there are stationary and roving mobs, in sets of three. These must be taken down. Any you miss will run into the central area when the Mag fight begins.\n\nLooking at the damage they deal I suspect that even a well geared Cataclysm DK tank would be advised to do this preliminary clear, at this stage of the game.\n\n2) Next you enter his circular lair. There are these single mobs spread around, seeming to channel his bonds. They have cubes. You do not click the cubes and never will be able to click the cubes. Just eye candy.\n\nAgro one of the channeling mobs. That causes all to run at you. They heal each other. Devise your own strategy to nuke them down. I popped Bloodlust etc and used my stone golem and Feral Spirit too.\n\nYou need to kill as many as possible so that few remain when the fight automatically shifts into the second phase. I had two left.\n\n3) Phase three begins after a while - Mags activates automatically. Stand with your back against a wall. Do not move. You will notice his attacks \"trying\" to move you. Always be doing something to ensure threat is maintained.\n\nObviously tank and spank. You know your own class for when you need to heal through damage. If you do not have an okay level 85 set of gear then the average player should just forget it. Your basic Mists questing greens will suffice.", "date": "2011-11-13T01:14:47-06:00", "rating": 9, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Good tips and good advice. To anyone a bit stressed about this; at level 85 as feral tank druid in mixed dps/tank gear, my health didn't get below 95% at any time. No potions, didn't use Regen or any of my other \"Oh crap\" buttons.", "creationdate": "2012-04-15T14:59:41-05:00", "id": 536140, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1570819, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Stompa", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "To any Guild Leaders of new or super casual guilds, this is an excellent mini Raid to cut your teeth on and get to know each other. I always bring the newer guildies here and then head on over to Gruul's and then step up again to TK or do a charity run for someone in the group by way of an Obsidium Sanctum \"10 man 3D\". Nice way to bond together, score a swag of achievements and someone scores a cool mount too!", "creationdate": "2012-08-08T19:06:34-05:00", "id": 562476, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1570819, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Taraezor", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-11-20T06:21:54-06:00", 2, "Taraezor"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 129, "id": 1583126, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "sorsa", "body": "[b]Tips for the soloing Fury Warrior:[/b]\r\n\r\nThe best setup for soloing Maggy as fury, is being Titan's Grip specced with 3/3 Bloodcraze. Icing on the cake but not totally necessary for this fight, is bringing a spare set of two-handers both enchanted with Mending (though if you plan to do soloing past T4 content, dual-Mending will allow you to kill bosses that would otherwise be near impossible to solo as Fury. It has allowed me to solo some pretty tough customers, for example Gorefiend in BT).\r\n\r\nIf you are from the future and have managed to grab one or two Souldrinkers from the Dragon Soul raid, then SMF becomes the stronger solo choice, due to the incredible self-healing proc from this 1-handed weapon.\r\n\r\nAfter ensuring you have all you need to survive Mag's damage (food buffs, drums and elixirs/flasks always help), the next step is getting used to killing the heals-spamming Channelers before Mag activates. 2 approaches I can suggest to this:\r\n\r\n1 - Go ape sh1t with aoe, popping DW+Reck and make them spread their long cd heals all over the place, just keep aoeing and they will drop like flies, then pick off any stragglers.\r\n2 - Take them 1 by 1. Bring an add down to just above 50%, pool 100 rage, pop CS + Inner Rage and blow it up, move on to next (with FL level gear you probably won't even need CS to burst them fast enough).\r\n\r\nIf the Channelers went down smoothly and Mag hasn't activated yet, you can use the short break to bandage  up. Once he attacks, it's tank and spank while keeping your back against a wall. Try to keep Thunderclap and Demo shout up. If you brought dual-Mending and Blood Craze, you may now proceed to point and lol and enjoy your loot.", "date": "2011-11-29T06:45:52-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 130, "id": 1594789, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "TheRealLink", "body": "Finally came back and didn't have too much trouble with this as a (now mostly) PvP upgraded 85 Fury Warrior.  Had what I thought was ok gear before at ~ilevel 348 but couldn't kill the healers in time.\n\nCame back after awhile with ilevel 372 and while the healers can still easily outheal the damage, there is enough strong burst damage to take them out.  Killed 2 before Mag became released, then dropped the other 3 fairly quickly along the wall once they couldn't keep up with the heals.\n\nMag himself was well, not quite a pushover but incredibly easy.  Maybe did 50K to me total or so - nothing of any special note.  Just fought him against a side wall and was fine.  Got ~50 gold, a 20-slot bag, his head, and other misc gear along with an achievement ;)\n\nWhile this place certainly hasn't given me quite as much headache as say, MC, it is certainly nice to get a raid crossed off the list.", "date": "2011-12-12T03:20:33-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-12-12T03:26:37-06:00", 1, "TheRealLink"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 131, "id": 1595134, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "PierreBalage", "body": "Soloed as Feral DPS druid 378ilvl, keep in bear form and keep Savage Defense up. Easy.:-)", "date": "2011-12-12T19:08:33-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 132, "id": 1598422, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "wikkedhead", "body": "Cannot solo this as 378iLvl Assassination Rogue.\n\nI can burn down 1 channeler at the start, but the pummeling from infernals & such is just too much ater that.\n\n\n*edit*\nTried it as Sub, and oddly enough, I did it.\n\nPremed/SS/Ambush/hemo/evisc...hemo/evisc.....1 down.\nFor the rest of them, I just hemo'd to get 5cps, autoattacked until ~50% health, evisc, then hemo/evisc to finish them off. It worked 90% of the time. Tossed in a Recup here & there, had to blow Evasion too.\n\nMags posed no threat alone, kept up recup/snd/expose armor/rupture. In that order of importance.\nThrew in a Feint here & there, had Evasion up again, CoS when he was doing blast nova if it was up.\n\nI win.", "date": "2011-12-18T14:12:02-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-12-18T14:26:53-06:00", 2, "wikkedhead"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 133, "id": 1612297, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "bruenir", "body": "Duo'ed with SV Hunter and Elemental Shammy (ilvl 390+ on both).  Cleared the mobs (which are ? even to an 85, which doesn't make sense) in the hall, then started the combat with one channeler.  The channelers summon elementals who were causing us some grief, but between aoe and some single target all adds were down by phase 2.  Once Mags engaged it got a lot simpler, though there were some infernals who stuck around and beat on the shammy. Took a few minutes for the kill.", "date": "2012-01-16T15:10:40-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 134, "id": 1612707, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "RagingNerd", "body": "Solo'd this today as a prot paladin.  Very easy, just tedious.  Ran Seal of Truth for most of the fight and if I got low (70k) I would swap to Insight.  But I was in no danger of ever dying.  Most annoying thing is the trash.  383 average I-level.", "date": "2012-01-17T14:10:20-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 135, "id": 1617319, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "936435", "body": "I was able to solo him on my shaman in elemental spec. I used the earth elemental totem to tank the trash in the room first, then popped heroism and nuked him as hard as I could. Glyph of unleashed lightning helped a ton to stay out of his way, and it took a lot of self-healing and rockbiter weapon to survive, especially since my ilvl is only 385, and it's all resto gear.", "date": "2012-01-26T21:54:42-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-01-26T21:56:40-06:00", 1, "936435"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 136, "id": 1619011, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Romance", "body": "I soloed this today (01-2012), it took about 10 minutes as a prot paladin (level 85). I used seal of insight to keep my health up easier, and kept tanking the adds untill Mag was dead. The boss dropped about 50g (so it's not 500g anymore!) and about 150g from drops. It is possible, doesn't take too long and if you need you get a nice 20 slot bag.", "date": "2012-01-30T14:09:19-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 137, "id": 1629736, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "909596", "body": "I was able to solo this guy as a Feral in full ilvl 390 PvP gear. \r\n\r\nMainly, you have to try and get the 4 warlocks down as fast as possible, which they do go down pretty fast while in kitty form. Do not swipe spam on them though, as they do heal, and you wont get them down that way. The extra damage that they deal is something you really dont want to deal with.\r\n\r\n\r\nAfter they go down, put your bleeds up on Mag, use a healing touch from predatory swiftness, and hop in bear form. Repeat as much as possible, keeping your bleeds up at all times. He will go down eventually.\r\n\r\nIt was about a 5-10 minute fight for me though though, I didnt really calculate it, so be prepared for that.", "date": "2012-02-21T05:10:32-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Going to attempt this, post how long it takes me soon...", "creationdate": "2012-03-03T12:25:37-06:00", "id": 524401, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1629736, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "917705", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 138, "id": 1640270, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "lyom", "body": "Soloed as a drood with my friend (locklock). This strategy worked for me: You pull the first add at the entrance door, and all run to you. \r\n\r\nThen the lock pulls one off you with high DPS. They may get a heal off until the lock has enough hate to peel the mob to them. He than ran across the room (Dark Manning has range greater than 30 yds despite what it says here! Just 30 yds is not enough) and nukes it down, using Felhunter to interrupt the casts.\r\n\r\nRepeat for all other adds. Once all adds are down, simply nuke Mag until he dies. Funny fact: When Mag dies, he vaporized on drood (only armor was left and fell to the floor) but for my friend it still showed the dragon as corpse.\r\n\r\nAnd then, proceed to cut off the [url=http://www.wowhead.com/item=34845]bags[/url] from his hide.", "date": "2012-03-16T13:08:51-05:00", "rating": -6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Solo means doing it [u]ALONE[/u]", "creationdate": "2012-04-12T13:21:52-05:00", "id": 535279, "rating": 4, "commentid": 1640270, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "SpiderX3m", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 139, "id": 1641762, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "spykemail", "body": "Has anyone succeeded in soloing this as a mage? If so, how? I can kill the adds but Mag has too much HP and I have no heals. I'm thinking about trying to tank him with my water elemental but it sounds extremely slow / prone to failure. Any ideas?\n\nTo kill the adds, have your water elemental attack a couple, pop cool downs, overwhelm them one at a time, counter heal if you see it. Keep the infernals away with a freeze. Shouldn't be too hard as long as you don't take damage from more than a couple and stay away from the infernals.", "date": "2012-03-20T06:32:18-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-03-20T06:41:45-05:00", 1, "spykemail"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 140, "id": 1642212, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "962249", "body": "Solo'd as bm spec with item lvl 382 gear.\r\n\r\nTook about 6 mins total. I used a spirit beast for healing and had glyph of misdirect so my pet always had aggro of all the adds. \r\n\r\nRan in and and went to the far part of the room then sent my pet to the add closest to the door to start then feign so they all went for him. Misdirected and pop bestial wrath and cd and just rapid fire multi shot all the adds. Once mag was fighting and the infernals were out just misdirected all again to my pet and let him tank them all and ignored the infernals.\r\n\r\nWith glyph of mend pet my pet was barely taking any damage and if the infernals aggro to me i just feigned and remisdirected the infernals hit for about 1,500 to 1,700 and with my pet healing me i barely got under 95% health.\r\n\r\nTrue you now only get 50g for the kill and about another 75g+ for selling drops. I did it for the t4 chest for transmoging. If your looking to solo for decent gold Molten core runs take no time and still drop 50g+ per boss so worth it for your time. \r\n\r\nAlso if your looking to have the full t4 set for transmog soloing the other 2 raids (grulls lair and Kara ) are also a breeze for a hunter and i'm sure other classes so always fun.", "date": "2012-03-21T14:21:28-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 16384, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 141, "id": 1643323, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "passolargo", "body": "I soloed him yesterday as a 85 Prot Paladin with 353 iLevel gear.\r\n\r\nClear the trash groups and engade Magtheridon, don't even bother with the adds. Seal of Insight and Word of Glory on cooldown and I didn't drop below 70% health. Used Hammer of the Righteous instead of Crusader Strike to kill off the Infernals.\r\n\r\nOn my first attempt I just let him knock me around and he despawned at 2%. On my second attempt, I put my back against the wall oposite to the door and just stayed there. No sweat.\r\n\r\nDropped around 51 gold, 20 slot epic bag, bag of gems, 3 tokens, his head and another random item.", "date": "2012-03-23T06:38:33-05:00", "rating": -2, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 142, "id": 1653498, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Esploratore", "body": "After having soloed it at around 380 item level, with more or less all I could try him (done first as fury dual wield, didn't lose more than half hp during the fight, done in fury with a shield and a gurthalak, ended up full hp, done as arms and finished at around 40k), tried also on my dk at around 350 item level, I couldn't kill the adds, so I just killed him outhealing all; was quite challenging.\r\n\r\nNow that my dk has 389 dps item level, 381 tank item level and my warrior has 392 dps this boss is not a challenge any more, so I thought to do an interesting thing that I haven't read on this thread from anyone so far: [b]soloing him completely during the enrage![/b] With my dk, of course.\r\n\r\nSo, I tried the other time in dps gear, around 386 item level, it took him 2 mins to bring me from 100% to 20% and I just kept healing myself with lichborne, after 22 mins he enraged and literally destroyed me with 15-16k hits and also very fast. I managed to do him 1 millions damage in enrage.\r\n\r\nNow new try in full tank gear, after he enraged I started kiting him, it's slighly harder than patchwerk for who soloed him; does a bit more damage and has more or less the same speed. Blast nova hits 15k each sec when enraged, but nonetheless that is a time to heal back: ams, rune tap, ghoul and sacrifice or lichborne and spam death coil yourself.\r\n\r\nIt's extremely challenging, took me 4 mins to kill him since I started to dps him, and I thought it was interesting to do as like I said magtheridon is now a pushover even for warriors.\r\n\r\nHere is some screenshots, as I cba making videos; all to show my hp vs his and maybe some of his hits, except the second one which shows the berserk effect.\r\n\r\nhttp://imageshack.us/f/443/magtheridonenragedsolo1h.jpg/\r\nhttp://imageshack.us/f/854/magtheridonenragedsolo2.jpg/\r\nhttp://imageshack.us/f/38/magtheridonenragedsolo3.jpg/\r\nhttp://imageshack.us/f/859/magtheridonenragedsolo4.jpg/\r\nhttp://imageshack.us/f/14/magtheridonenragedsolo5.jpg/\r\nhttp://imageshack.us/f/191/magtheridonenragedsolo6.jpg/\r\nhttp://imageshack.us/f/207/magtheridonenragedsolo7.jpg/", "date": "2012-04-13T19:57:59-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-04-13T20:01:05-05:00", 2, "Esploratore"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 143, "id": 1654394, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Karatir", "body": "Easily soloable as a 381 geared combat rogue with 378 weapons. I just ran in there, used AR with blade flurry on and all the channelers eventually died and then it was ezpz on the boss, just keep recup going and you'll be good to go.", "date": "2012-04-15T13:13:14-05:00", "rating": -2, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
