{"commentv2": 1, "number": 145, "id": 1669427, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Mendric", "body": "Just wanted to add to those thinking of making this a weekly solo. Whether or not its worth it, is up to you and your time. For me, I play a lot so may do this weekly, but not really much in[u]cent[/u]ive (for me). The gold has been greatly lowered (no more 500g peops).\r\n\r\nHere's a list of what dropped for me just now (I also posted a screenshot of the loot).\r\n\r\n[b]Loot + Vendor value[u][/u][/b]\r\n\r\nGold = [i]49g 88s 98c[/i]\r\nTotal after vending loot (including Gems) = 130g 54s 57c\r\n\r\n[url=item=32386]Magtheridon\u2019s Head[/url] - This starts the quest [url=quest=11003]\"The fall of Magtheridon\u2019\"[/url].\r\nQuest reward = $13g 20s (as 85 capped (no xp)). Choice of ring ([url=item=28792]1[/url], [url=item=28793]2[/url], [url=item=28790]3[/url], [url=item=28791]4[/url]) worth \r\n6g 2s 56c.\r\n\r\n[url=item=34845]Pit Lord's Satchel[/url] - 20 slot bag.\r\n87s 50c\r\n*What is it with Blizz, and the fact that most bags that drop are under 1g? Hehe\r\n\r\n[url=item=28779]Girdle of the Endless Pit[/url].\r\n4g 24s 94c\r\n\r\n[url=item=28781]Karaborian Talisman[/url]\r\n20g 30s 59c\r\n\r\n[url=item=29755]Chestguard of the Fallen Hero[/url]\r\n5g\r\n\r\n[url=item=29753]Chestguard of the Fallen Defender[/url] x2\r\n10g (5x2)\r\n\r\n[url=item=34846]Black Sack of Gems[/url].\r\nThe gems that I got were:\r\n\r\n[url=item=32229]Lionseye[/url] 5g\r\n[url=item=32228]Empyrean Sapphire[/url] 5g\r\n[url=item=32231]Pyrestone[/url] 5g\r\n[url=item=23439]Noble Topaz[/url] 3g\r\n[url=item=23440]Dawnstone[/url] 3g\r\n\r\n*AH these if you want, but being there are much better gems now, doubt you'll get much business.\r\n\r\nSo being that the quest can only be done once (of course), in your consideration of making your [s]millions[/s] hundreds here, be sure to subtract the full quest givings of 19g 22s 56c. This is just my outcome so your numbers may be slightly better, good luck.\r\n\r\nFor those thinking of soloing this as an 85, just don't fall asleep. Meaning it's easy (well, I did it on my prot Pali also). I came here looking for the mechanics of the fight then got tired of looking so just went for it. Wow, was I amazed how simple it went. Having just returned to wow in 3 years, I wanted to reminisce these old fights. My guild did it back in BC. I did it for that reason, and not for the loot really, so seeing what it is now, you can see if it's worth your time.", "date": "2012-05-21T21:59:15-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 146, "id": 1677057, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "1000135", "body": "[b]Easy solo by rogue combat 390 item level, patch 4.3.4[/b]", "date": "2012-06-15T18:52:03-05:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 147, "id": 1680108, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "gerbera", "body": "I'll add my soloing comments, both as a [b]feral bear[/b] with 350 iLvl, and as a [b]survival hunter[/b] with 385 iLvl.\r\n\r\nThe bear only had various gear from 5-man heroics and JP purchase items. My dps was way too low to kill any of the Channelers (I'm also terrible at cat dps, so I didn't even bother trying that). I think I got one to ~1000 hp when it was healed to full by its friends. After the [b]2 minute[/b] mark, Magtheridon himself becomes active whether or not the Channelers are dead. I ended up just tanking him, the Channelers, and several of their Abyssals until the boss was dead. The bear dodge and self heal is such that I never went below 90% hp, and even that was because of the bouncing around during the earthquake.\r\n\r\nFor the hunter, I just use a tank pet (turtle), blow all cooldowns on the Channelers, and eventually the combined damage of all the dots, pet aoe, multishot, and a trap is just too much for the healing to keep up with and they all die. Then just the boss is left.\r\n\r\nGood luck everyone.", "date": "2012-06-23T09:13:19-05:00", "rating": -4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 148, "id": 1686219, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Balla0529", "body": "Marksmanship (7/31/3) Hunter.\r\nBallinhunts, of Kargath-US.\r\n409 iLvl\r\n\r\nUsing a turtle as the \"Go-To\" [b]tenacity[/b] pet, I find it easy to solo (duo really) all of the old content as an appropriately-spec'ed [b]Marksmanship[/b] Hunter.\r\n\r\nI advise the use of [b]Glyph of Mending[/b] and [b]Glyph of Misdirection[/b] as two critical Major Glyphs, the other choices are yours to make.\r\n\r\nAs has been previously mentioned, [i]Magtheridon[/i] is indeed a pushover.\r\n\r\nSend your (tenacity) pet in, allowing him to develop instant-threat. Once all of the [i]Hellfire Channeler[/i]'s have amassed your pet, Misdirect and Multi-Shot (throw in an Explosive Trap to spice things up a bit) to your heart's content - eventually they'll all fall down! Now, Feign Death and allow your pet to gain [i]Magtheridon[/i]'s aggro and to redirect the [i]Burning Abyssals[/i] to your pet; once again, simply Misdirect and win. [u]Don't forget to switch to Aspect of the Fox when you start getting bounced around![/u]\r\n\r\nUse Feign Death often!\r\n\r\nIf you have any questions, feel free to contact me in-game!", "date": "2012-07-09T03:17:08-05:00", "rating": -4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 149, "id": 1701792, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "TheSonicGod", "body": "Soloed as a lv90 Windwalker Monk in the MoP Beta. Just kept self-healing and brought out Xuen to help fight for more DPS. Was done in 2 minutes. Pretty amusing. :)", "date": "2012-08-19T15:08:55-05:00", "rating": -6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 150, "id": 1713768, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Troubadour", "body": "Solo'ed as a Demonology Warlock with [spell=114168]  in 360's gear, using  [spell=112867].\r\n\r\nCleared the adds outsides the cage, engaged and couldn't kill any of the adds.\r\n\r\nJust let the Voidlord tank, healing him with health funnel (glyphed) in every cd, and focus on Mag.\r\n\r\nWhen hp hit 50%, spammed mass drain life (talented) until health was full, using healthstone if its not on cd.\r\n\r\nWhen went out of healthstones, used  [spell=104773] and got brand new ones.\r\n\r\nWhen Voidlord died (forgot some health funnels), just summoned a new one (instant cast, almost entirely fight had demonic fury almost capped).\r\n\r\nNever enter Metamorphosis, because it drains all of your demonic fury.\r\n\r\nCurious fact: When the fight ended, had about 15 stacks of Molten Core procs.", "date": "2012-09-14T22:34:14-05:00", "rating": -6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
